# Voice rules — blocks Edit/Write content that matches these regex patterns.
#
# Copy this file to .voice-rules.local (gitignored) and uncomment / add the
# patterns your partner's voice rules prohibit. The hook scripts/hooks/
# voice-rules.ts reads .voice-rules.local on every Edit and Write and
# blocks the tool call (exit 2) if any pattern matches.
#
# This is the tier-1 enforcement equivalent of an identity-kernel voice
# rule. Auto-memory rules drift under context pressure; this doesn't.
#
# One regex per line. Lines starting with # are comments. Patterns are
# JavaScript regex (not grep). No enforcement if this file doesn't exist.
#
# Examples (uncomment or customize):
#
# [—–]                         # em dash / en dash
# \bhonestly\b                           # implies the alternative
# \bto be transparent\b                  # same class
# \bI'll be frank\b                      # framing before truth
